The article is a transcript of a press briefing given by White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs on August 12, 2009. The briefing covered various topics including upcoming speeches by U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations Susan Rice and President Obama, the situation in Afghanistan, executive compensation, healthcare reform, and the Medal of Freedom awards. Gibbs addressed concerns about misinformation and disinformation being spread during the healthcare reform debate. He also discussed the importance of having civil discussions and debates without resorting to personal attacks or degrading comments.